{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"PeriodicSyncManager","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncManager","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Periodic_Background_Synchronization_API\">Web Periodic Background Synchronization API</a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Interfaces</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncEvent\"><code>PeriodicSyncEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncManager\"><code>PeriodicSyncManager</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ServiceWorkerRegistration/periodicSync\"><code>ServiceWorkerRegistration.periodicSync</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ServiceWorkerGlobalScope/onperiodicsync\"><code>ServiceWorkerGlobalScope.onperiodicsync</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Events</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ServiceWorkerGlobalScope/periodicsync_event\"><code>ServiceWorkerGlobalScope</code>: <code>periodicsync</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <strong><code>PeriodicSyncManager</code></strong> interface of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Periodic_Background_Synchronization_API\"><code>Web Periodic Background Synchronization API</code></a> provides a way to register tasks to be run in a service worker at periodic intervals with network connectivity. These tasks are referred to as periodic background sync requests. Access <code>PeriodicSyncManager</code> through the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ServiceWorkerRegistration/periodicSync\"><code>ServiceWorkerRegistration.periodicSync</code></a>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"properties","title":"Properties","isH3":false,"content":"<p>None.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"methods","title":"Methods","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"periodicsyncmanager.register\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncManager/register\"><code>PeriodicSyncManager.register</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Registers a periodic sync request with the browser with the specified tag and options. Returns a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>Promise</code></a> that resolves when the registration completes.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"periodicsyncmanager.gettags\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncManager/getTags\"><code>PeriodicSyncManager.getTags</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>Promise</code></a> that resolves with a list of <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\"><code>strings</code></a> representing the tags that are currently registered for periodic syncing.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"periodicsyncmanager.unregister\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncManager/unregister\"><code>PeriodicSyncManager.unregister</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Unregisters the periodic sync request corresponding to the specified tag and returns a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>Promise</code></a> that resolves when unregistration completes.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>The following examples show how to use the interface.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"requesting_a_periodic_background_sync","title":"Requesting a Periodic Background Sync","isH3":true,"content":"<p>The following asynchronous function registers a periodic background sync at a minimum interval of one day from a browsing context:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">async</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">registerPeriodicNewsCheck</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> registration <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">await</span> navigator<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>serviceWorker<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>ready<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">try</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">await</span> registration<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>periodicSync<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">register</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'get-latest-news'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token literal-property property\">minInterval</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">24</span> <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> <span class=\"token number\">60</span> <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> <span class=\"token number\">60</span> <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> <span class=\"token number\">1000</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">catch</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'Periodic Sync could not be registered!'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"verifying_a_background_periodic_sync_by_tag","title":"Verifying a Background Periodic Sync by Tag","isH3":true,"content":"<p>This code checks to see if a Periodic Background Sync task with a given tag is registered.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>navigator<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>serviceWorker<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>ready<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">then</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">registration</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  registration<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>periodicSync<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getTags</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">then</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">tags</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>tags<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">includes</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'get-latest-news'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n      <span class=\"token function\">skipDownloadingLatestNewsOnPageLoad</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"removing_a_periodic_background_sync_task","title":"Removing a Periodic Background Sync Task","isH3":true,"content":"<p>The following code removes a Periodic Background Sync task to stop articles syncing in the background.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>navigator<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>serviceWorker<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>ready<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">then</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">registration</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  registration<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>periodicSync<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">unregister</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'get-latest-news'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://wicg.github.io/periodic-background-sync/#periodicsyncmanager-interface","title":"Web Periodic Background Synchronization"}],"query":"api.PeriodicSyncManager"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.PeriodicSyncManager","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncManager/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://web.dev/periodic-background-sync/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Richer offline experiences with the Periodic Background Sync API</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://webplatformapis.com/periodic_sync/periodicSync_improved.html\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">A Periodic Background Sync demo app</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Properties","id":"properties"},{"text":"Methods","id":"methods"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The PeriodicSyncManager interface of the Web Periodic Background Synchronization API provides a way to register tasks to be run in a service worker at periodic intervals with network connectivity. These tasks are referred to as periodic background sync requests. Access PeriodicSyncManager through the ServiceWorkerRegistration.periodicSync.","popularity":0.0007,"modified":"2022-01-27T16:52:19.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/periodicsyncmanager","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/periodicsyncmanager/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/516c74d03bd44861eca7da5a96d287aef846b89d","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncManager","title":"PeriodicSyncManager"}],"pageTitle":"PeriodicSyncManager - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}